      <section eId="sec_CCRP-834">
        <num>CCRP 834</num>
        <heading>834. Â When presence of defendant not necessary</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-834__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The making, hearing of, or ruling on a preliminary motion or application addressed to the court;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-834__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The making, hearing of, or ruling on a motion or application addressed to the court during the trial when the jury is not present; except as provided in Clause</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-834__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of Article 831; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-834__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The making, hearing of, or ruling on a motion or application made after his conviction.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112824</p>
